      <description>&lt;p&gt;Ever since I first saw a cinemagraph on Reddit, I&amp;rsquo;ve always wanted to make one.
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The stars aligned and when I visited Lamu, I actually remembered. With possible cinemagraphs in mind, I took a bunch of pictures in my camera&amp;rsquo;s continuous shooting mode.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Realizing that creating a full cinemagraph would be a decent amount of work, I first threw them onto Google photos, which has an automatic animation utility in Assistant. This would help me weed out the photos that wouldn&amp;rsquo;t look good anyways. Here&amp;rsquo;s how they turned out:&lt;/p&gt;

